  "event_preview": "Albert Park Circuit in its current form is measured at 5.278 km (3.280 mi), featuring 16 turns running clockwise around Albert Park Lake in Melbourne, Australia. The circuit hosts the Australian Grand Prix - traditionally one of the season's first rounds. Following the 2021 COVID-19 cancellation, the layout was significantly revised, with the Turn 9-10 chicane replaced by a fast sweeping complex, and several corners widened to improve safety and overtaking opportunities. The track features four DRS zones and is known for its rapidly evolving grip levels, as the semi-permanent surface built on public roads gains rubber throughout the weekend. The official race lap record stands at 1:19.813, set by Charles Leclerc for Ferrari during the 2024 Australian Grand Prix, while the all-time fastest lap belongs to Lando Norris, who clocked a 1:15.096 in Q3 qualifying for the 2025 race.",
